title: [Blighted Forest, Treetop]
description: A natural stair is formed by overlapping branches, offering passage from the branches of one oak to its neighboring trees.  Leaves sway gently at the touch of a light breeze and birds flitter from limb to limb.  Below, dense growths of ferns and rhododendrons created an emerald splash amid the drab greys and browns of the forest floor.

A natural stair is formed by overlapping branches, offering passage from the branches of one oak to its neighboring trees.  Black leaves sway gently at the touch of a light breeze and tree frogs sing to the moon.  Below, dense growths of ferns and rhododendrons created a dark emerald splash amid the shadows on the forest floor.
